title: Man trapped in NSW dam with his nose just above the water - Yahoo7
text:
Man trapped in NSW dam with his nose just above the water Catherine Healey and AAP - Yahoo7 News on February 7, 2017, 5:01 pm Share Man trapped in NSW dam with his nose just above the water - Yahoo7 A man had an amazing escape after he was trapped in a dam at a farm on the NSW north coast. Close Incredible survival story after man trapped by excavator UP NEXT VIDEO Incredible survival story after man trapped by excavator. Source: 7 News Incredible survival story after man trapped by excavator 
Daniel Miller was pinned under a 3.5-tonne excavator at his Charlotte Bay property near Forster for two hours on Tuesday, before a neighbour heard his cries for help. 
The 45-year-old was trapped with his nose just above the water, after the excavator rolled into the dam. Daniel Miller was trapped for two hours with his nose above water. Source: 7 News A neighbour heard Mr Miller's cries for help and called in firefighters. Source: 7 News 
The Rural Fire Service was forced to pump out water from the dam so Mr Miller could be released. 
Westpac Rescue Helicopter air crewman Graham Nickisson told AAP Mr Miller had been crying out for help for two hours before a woman heard him and alerted emergency services. Rescuers were forced to pump out the dam. Source: 7 News 
Rescue crews say if it had of rained while Mr Miler was trapped, he could have drowned. 
The 45-year-old was taken to John Hunter Hospital in Newcastle for treatment to "minor injuries", including a sore back and potential hypothermia. The rescue scene near Forster. Source: 7 News
